Mary Berry has discovered that baking is her genes - after learning her great-great-grandfather was a baker at a 19th century workhouse.

Unbeknown to the Great British Bake Off judge - who is taking part in the BBC1 programme Who Do You Think You Are? - her ancestor Robert Houghton ran a bakery in Norwich in the 19th century, in an area awash with prostitutes and criminals. 

He ran the thriving bakery for nearly 40 years, researchers found, and had a contract to supply a workhouse in the city.

